<div id="pf32" class="pf w2 h0" data-page-no="32"><div class="pc pc32 w2 h0"><img class="bi x0 y0 w3 h1" alt="" src="bg32.png"/><div class="t m0 x34 h2 y231 ff54 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">49</div><div class="t m11 x31 h26 y52b ff52 fs1e fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">T<span class="_ _15"></span><span class="ff53 fs1f">u<span class="_ _11"></span>e<span class="_ _15"> </span>s<span class="_ _15"> </span>d<span class="_ _15"> </span>a<span class="_ _15"></span>y</span></div><div class="t m12 x2d h20 y259 ff54 fs1a fc0 sc0 ls8 ws3e">August 6</div><div class="t m0 x23 h27 y25a ff57 fs20 fc0 sc0 lsa ws50">True Repentance and Confession</div><div class="t m10 x3 h23 y5d8 ff56 fs0 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">What</div><div class="t m0 x30 h24 y5d8 ff57 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws84"> spiritual principles do we learn from Leviticus 5:5; 1 John 1:9; </div><div class="t m0 x23 h24 y5fb ff57 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws91">Isaiah 1:16–18; and Acts 26:19, 20 regarding the nature of true </div><div class="t m0 x23 h24 y5fc ff57 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws1">repentance and confession?</div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y5fd ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">____________<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__<span class="_ _16"></span>__<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y5fe ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">____________<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__<span class="_ _16"></span>__<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y5ff ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">____________<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__<span class="_ _16"></span>__<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x2b h5 y5de ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws4f">Genuine repentance is always accompanied by confession of spe<span class="ws0">-</span></div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y5df ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws8a">cific sins. The Holy Spirit does not give us vague feelings of guilt. He </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y5e0 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws1">convicts us of our definite shortcomings. </div><div class="t m0 x2b h5 y5e1 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws10b">“True confession is always of a specific character, and acknowl<span class="ws0">-</span></div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y5e2 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws58">edges particular sins. They may be of such a nature as to be brought </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y5e3 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws118">before God only; they may be wrongs that should be confessed to </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y5e4 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsac">individuals who have suffered injury through them; or they may be </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y5e5 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws107">of a public character, and should then be as publicly confessed. But </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y5e6 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsbf">all confession should be definite and to the point, acknowledging the </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y5e7 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsf2">very sins of which you are guilty.”—Ellen G. White, <span class="ff54">Steps to Christ, </span></div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y5e8 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws1">p. 38.  </div><div class="t m0 x2b h5 y600 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws35">The purpose of the convicting power of the Holy Spirit is to reveal </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y601 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws44">our need of the saving grace of Christ. Repentance does not make </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y602 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsfd">God love us more; rather, it enables us to appreciate His love more. </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y603 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws106">Confession does not earn God’s forgiveness; it instead enables us to </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y604 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws57">receive His forgiveness. God does not love us more when we repent </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y605 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws97">or love us less when we fail to. His love for us is constant. The only </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y606 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws13e">variable is our response to the working of the Holy Spirit in our </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y607 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws1">lives.  </div><div class="t m0 x2b h5 y608 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws12">The truth is that our hearts are hindered from receiving the abundant </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y609 ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws3f">blessings that God has for us while our spiritual arteries are clogged </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y60a ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsa3">with the sludge of sin. Sin deadens us to the Spirit’s prompting and </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y60b ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws44">makes it harder for us to respond to Him. Repentance and confes<span class="ws0">-</span></div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y60c ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws69">sion open the clogged channels of our spiritual hearts so that we may </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y60d ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws1">receive the overflowing of the Holy Spirit’s presence and power. </div><div class="t m0 x2b h5 y60e ff55 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws1">   </div><div class="t m0 x2e h24 y60f ff57 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws118">However much we long for forgiveness when we confess and </div><div class="t m0 x2e h24 y610 ff57 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsb0">repent, we must remember that this is a two-way street.  That </div><div class="t m0 x2e h24 y611 ff57 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws79">is, how do we respond to those who have treated us wrongly </div><div class="t m0 x2e h24 y612 ff57 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws61">and who ask for forgiveness? Who, though totally undeserving </div><div class="t m0 x2e h24 y613 ff57 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsec">of our forgiveness, do we need to forgive anyway, and why is it </div><div class="t m0 x2e h24 y614 ff57 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws1">so important for us to forgive?</div><div class="t m0 x2e h24 y280 ff57 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">________________________________<span class="_ _16"></span>______________________</div><div class="t m0 x2e h24 y615 ff57 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">________________________________<span class="_ _16"></span>______________________</div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
